 Anti-apartheid icon Archbishop
Emeritus Desmond Tutu's family hopes to have him home by next week, according
to the Desmond & Leah Tutu Legacy Foundation. Tutu is receiving
treatment for a "recurring infection" in Cape Town. The 88-year-old was
admitted to hospital on Wednesday, News24 reported. According
to a statement from the foundation, Leah Tutu said her husband was hospitalised
several times in recent years for the same infection.  Foundation
chairperson Niclas Kjellstrom-Matseke said the family was hopeful he would be
discharged from hospital by next week.  